<div class="mainhead"><a href="http://www.kk.org/cooltools/archives/001087.php">Energy smart power strip</a></div>
 
<div class="entrydate">01-11-06</div>
</div>
<h2><a href="http://www.kk.org/cooltools/archives/001087.php">Smart Power Strip</a></h2>

<div class="entrybody">

<p class="entryleadimage"><img src="http://www.kk.org/cooltools/archives/smart_strip.jpg" alt="" title="" /></p>


<p>This is so simple. You plug your PC into the main socket, and then plug your printer, scanner, monitor etc into the other sockets. When you turn off your computer, the smart unit shuts the power off to the other sockets. Saves power from constantly-on transformers, saves the environment, and saves lives from electrical fires caused by overheated DC adaptors. Also works for AV equipment.</p>










</div>


<div id="authordate">
<div class="subauthorname">-- Bruce Richardson &nbsp;</div>
<br clear="all" />
</div>



<div class="infofooter">
<p>Smart Strip Power Strip<br />
$31</p></div>


<div class="infofooter">
<p>Available from <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0006Q3B2W/ref=nosim/kkorg-20">Amazon</a></p></div>


<div class="infofooter">
<p>Also, there's the OneClick Power Strip available in the UK from<br />
<a href="http://www.oneclickpower.com/store/">OneClick</a></p></div>














